RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 1 1M All Weather Track CR: 89. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BRONZE WARRIOR broke alertly and established the early pace, was well handled while setting prompted fractions through the backstretch run, carved out a decent pace while pressured to the quarter marker, shook free in upper stretch, was confronted by LYING GHOST nearing the furlong marker, battled that foe while maintaining a narrow advantage into deep stretch and dug in in the final stages to prevail. LYING GHOST settled off of the decent early pace, was roused three wide along the second turn, confronted BRONZE WARRIOR nearing the furlong pole, gamely battled that rival while kept to steady urging, could not get by the determined winner in the final stages and was gamely bested, while clear of the rest. WALKING BOSS came in a bit tight leaving the start, took up and was off slowly, was unhurried through the early stages, was steered outside of rivals along the second turn, mounted a four wide rally into the stretch, gained ground at the furlong pole, could not keep pace with the top pair in the late stages and held safely at the end for third. MASHHAD FLATS was prominent into the first turn, prompted the decent fractions through the backstretch run, kept close attendance to BRONZE WARRIOR to the quarter marker, dropped back leaving the far turn and gave way in the drive. BROOKYS TAPIT settled off of the moderate early pace while saving ground, was well positioned into the second turn, gained ground at the quarter marker, could not sustain that bid into the stretch and lacked a late response.

ENTRY.NAME: Mashhad Flats
ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace,dropped back upper,gave way stretch

ENTRY.NAME: Brookys Tapit
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled inside,well placed,inside bid 1/4,failed to sustain bid

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 2 1M All Weather Track CR: 72. Claiming Purse 20000. FOR FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500, if for $10,500, allowed 2 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $10,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SWEET BLUSH stumbled at the start and was off a step slowly, was hustled to establish the early lead and dictated terms into the first turn, set decent fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, was confronted by PRANCIN N THE PARK at the quarter marker, shook free from that rival into upper stretch, extended the lead at the furlong grounds while kept to steady urging and drew clear in the final stages. PRANCIN N THE PARK broke out a step leaving the start, was forwardly placed into the first turn and attended to the pace into the backstretch run, tracked the decent fractions to the far turn, advanced to confront SWEET BLUSH nearing the quarter marker, lost ground to that rival into the drive, could not keep pace with the winner in deep stretch and bested the rest. BIG GIFT broke in at the start, bothered DUST MAKER and was off slowly, settled while saving ground in the early stages, swung to the three path into the backstretch run, advanced while two deep on the second turn, was steered three wide into the drive and ran evenly to mid-stretch, raced on the left lead into deep stretch, could not impact the top two in the final stages and kept on to secure third. DUST MAKER was bothered and took up at the start and was away slowly, settled off of the decent early pace while saving ground, chased in pursuit through the backstretch run, saved ground to the quarter marker, tipped two wide for the drive, lacked a response in the stretch and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Dust Maker
ENTRY.COMMENT: took up start,settled inside,2wide into stretch,gave way

ENTRY.NAME: Big Gift
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in start,2-3w 2nd turn,evenly to 1/8,no impact,ran on 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 3 1M All Weather Track CR: 98. Allowance Purse 33000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs. (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $50,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ASCENDANCY settled off of the decent early pace while never far back, inched closer along the backstretch run, was roused three wide into the second turn, rallied four wide into the drive, responded to firm urging while four deep in the stretch, took command nearing the sixteenth-marker and edged clear in the final stages. ANTHONYS CLEOPATRA hopped at the start and was off a step slowly, recovered to be just off of the early pace into the first turn, stalked three deep through the backstretch run, made a steady advance while outside of rivals into the far turn, raced three wide into the drive, vied for the lead at the furlong grounds, could not match strides with ASCENDANCY in deep stretch and kept on in the late stages to secure the place. TAM'S LITTLE ANGEL was sent at the start and established the lead into the first turn, set solid fractions while pressured through the backstretch run, was confronted by TROJAN CLUBHOUSE at the quarter marker, lost the lead to that rival into upper stretch, battled TROJAN CLUBHOUSE from the rail into mid-stretch, weakened in the final furlong and was outfinished for second while just holding for third. TWILIGHT EMPIRE lacked early speed, maintained a two wide path to the second turn, gained ground at the quarter marker, was steered three wide for the drive, continued to advance approaching the furlong marker, lacked a final bid in deep stretch and just missed for third. TROJAN CLUBHOUSE was forwardly placed into the first turn, prompted the solid fractions through the backstretch run, pressed the pacesetter to the quarter marker, took command in upper stretch and held a narrow lead to the furlong pole, could not keep pace in the late stages and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: Tam's Little Angel
ENTRY.OWNER: Williams Larry D and Williams Marianne

ENTRY.NAME: Twilight Empire
ENTRY.COMMENT: no early speed,gain 1/4,3w into stretch,no final kick,missed 3rd

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 4 1M Turf CR: 66. Maiden Claiming Purse 16000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $20,000, if for $18,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TOM'S PIC forwardly placed into the first turn, stalked the pace then assumed command into the backstretch run when CHROME'S BEST COPY drifted out, set decent fractions to the half-mile marker, showed the way to the quarter marker, opened to a clear lead into upper stretch, had the margin cut into in the final sixteenth, slightly jumped a bare patch in deep stretch and held in a drive at the end to prevail. FRESNO CHILE stalked the decent early pace from the inside, saved all of the ground to the second turn, was a bit green while chasing TOM'S PIC to the furlong pole, switched to the correct lead inside of the furlong marker, closed well in deep stretch, could not reel in the winner in the final stages and held for second. JACQUELINE COCHRAN settled just off of the early pace while in the second flight, raced outside of a rival through the backstretch run, came two wide into the far turn, angled four wide into upper stretch, lost ground in the run to the furlong marker, re-rallied in deep stretch, closed willingly in the final stages and just missed for second, while getting up in time for third. I'M GONNA SHINE unhurried in the early stages, saved ground to the second turn, came in a bit tight and steadied approaching the top of the lane, rallied along the inside in the drive, finished well and just missed for the minor awards. CHROME'S BEST COPY broke alertly and showed good early speed, set the pace into the first turn, drifted out nearing the six-furlong pole, recovered into the backstretch run and attended to the decent pace, kept close attendance to TOM'S PIC to the second turn, lost position into the drive and tired. SILVER FLIRT settled just off of the early pace, raced four wide along the first turn then moved to the three path for the backstretch run, tracked the pace while outside of rivals to the second turn, lost ground three wide on the far turn, was outrun in the drive and was not a late factor.

ENTRY.NAME: Chrome's Best Copy
ENTRY.OWNER: Mutiny Bay Backstretch LLC and Warlock Stables

ENTRY.NAME: Silver Flirt
ENTRY.OWNER: Packsaddle Road LLC and Baker, D. Wayne

Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Maiden, Claiming And Starter Races For $20,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) (Cal-Bred Or Cal-Sired Horses That Have Won The Open First Condition Allowance Race In North ern California Must Carry An Additional 2 lbs., Unless Entered for the Optional Claiming Price.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: STOIC LUNA was well placed into the first turn, saved ground while tracking the leaders through the backstretch run, inched closer along the second turn, angled three wide into upper stretch, loomed at the furlong pole, responded to urging and took command nearing the sixteenth-marker, kicked clear in deep stretch and won going away. PERSUASIVE LIPS was prominent into the first turn, attended to the pace into the backstretch run then pressed the decent pace to the half-mile pole, confronted SHEZAGHOST at the quarter marker and took a narrow lead into upper stretch, was set down while battling SHEZAGHOST to the furlong marker, was overtaken by STOIC LUNA nearing the sixteenth-pole, could not keep pace with the winner in the final stages and held safely in the end for second. SHEZAGHOST was hustled leaving the break and led into the first turn, set a pressured pace through the backstretch run, was confronted by PERSUASIVE LIPS nearing the quarter marker then was overtaken in upper stretch, battled with PERSUASIVE LIPS to the furlong marker, could not match strides with the top pair in the final furlong and weakened, while holding safely for third. VRONSKY FEINT forwardly placed into the first turn, chased the decent fractions from a three wide path through the backstretch run, improved position three wide on the far turn, could not sustain that bid in the stretch and gave way. BANDEENA settled off of the decent early pace, raced outside of a rival through the backstretch run, slipped to the inside heading to the second turn and did not threaten in the stretch. SHEZARUNAWAY lacked early speed, lagged through the backstretch run, was coaxed along two wide into the far turn and did not factor in the drive.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 6 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 74. Maiden Claiming Purse 14000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $12,500.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIVE O COCKTAIL forwardly placed in the early running, took back and was well placed while just off of the leaders into the turn, raced two wide to the quarter marker, was roused three wide into the drive, was full of run nearing the furlong marker, assumed command approaching the sixteenth-pole and drove clear in the final stages to prevail. DAWN AT LAST ducked in at the start and was off a bit slowly, was rushed up in the early stages and set the pace into the turn, set decent fractions to the quarter marker while well handled, extended the lead into mid-stretch, was overtaken by FIVE O COCKTAIL nearing the sixteenth-marker, could not keep pace with the winner in deep stretch and held well in the end for second. BARBERA stalked the decent early pace while outside of rivals, ran in pursuit of DAWN AT LAST while three then two wide into the turn, cut into the pacesetter's margin nearing the quarter pole, lost ground to DAWN AT LAST into upper stretch, was outkicked in the drive by the top pair and was clear of the rest in the end for third. STANDFORGRIT showed good early speed, lost the early lead to DAWN AT LAST and chased that rival to the turn, saved ground while chasing along the bend, lost position into upper stretch and could not muster the needed late response. AUTISM SHINE prominent in the early running, rated off of the early pace and slipped to the rail heading to the turn, saved ground to the top of the stretch and lacked a response in the drive. MO TOWN GAL chased the decent early pace, ran two wide to the quarter marker, was coaxed along three wide into the drive and did not threaten in the stretch. TUDOR'S FOREST chased the decent early pace while outside of rivals, came four wide into the drive, could not keep pace heading to mid-stretch and tired. PLEASANT WARNING bobbled at the start and was off slowly, lacked early speed into the turn and did not factor.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 7 1M Turf CR: 84. Starter Allowance Purse 22000. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $50,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Weight, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since March 1 Allowed 2 lbs. (One win for $25,000 or less will not be considered wh en determining eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: AZURE STAR (IRE) was sent after an alert beginning and dictated terms into the first turn, set decent fractions while well handled through the backstretch run, extended the lead along the second turn, was confronted by CHARBONNEAU in upper stretch, met that bid to the furlong marker, dueled to deep stretch, dug in under steady urging in the final stages and lasted at the wire for a game win. CHARBONNEAU was forwardly placed in the early running, stalked the decent fractions through the backstretch run, lost a bit of ground to AZURE STAR along the second turn, re-rallied and confronted AZURE STAR in upper stretch, battled with that foe to the furlong pole, dueled with his stablemate to deep stretch, could not get by the determined winner in the final sixteenth and was denied for the win, while besting the rest. DRUIDIC tracked the decent early pace from the second flight, saved ground through the backstretch run while well placed, lost ground along the second turn, ran evenly to the furlong marker, re-rallied in deep stretch, was not able to impact the top two in the final stages and was clear for third in the end. LORD OF LIGHT unhurried in the early stages, raced outside of a rival through the backstretch run, came two wide into the second turn, swung four wide into the drive, offered a mild late rally and improved position in the final stages. CHUCKANUT BAY allowed to settle early on, saved all of the ground through the backstretch run and into the second turn, tipped two wide for the drive and did not offer a late response. FLY WICKED EAGLE prominent in the early stages, took back to track the decent pace into the first turn, ran in pursuit while outside of a rival through the backstretch run, was outrun along the second turn, chased the leaders into the drive and gave way in the final furlong.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 8 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 91. Claiming Purse 15000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE SINCE APRIL 1 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250 (Claiming And Starter Races For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: GET'EM TIGER broke sharply and dueled for the early lead with O'NEILL'S LEGACY, backed off a bit past the five-furlong marker, re-engaged the leader on the turn, dueled down the stretch, got the advantage passing the furlong pole and drew off under a strong hand ride and intermittent urging. LADY IN A HURRY reserved early, stayed to the inside while making good forward progress through the turn, ran on well down the stretch despite racing mostly on the wrong lead, vied between runners into deep stretch and just got up for second. REINA DE REYES was away well, tracked the leading pair down the backstretch, waited until the quarter pole to launch a bid, came into the stretch three wide then ran on well to the finish, lost a bob for the place while no threat to the winner. O'NEILL'S LEGACY broke well and was hustled to the front, opened up to a clear advantage heading into the turn, met the challenge of GET'EM TIGER at the top of the stretch, dueled that one to the furlong grounds then weakened. SHOUT IT OUT outrun early, caught up to the pack on the turn, was forced wide and steadied sharply to avoid the loose horse near the five-sixteenths marker, was outrun into the stretch and lacked a late response. GARDEES WORLD broke in the air, hit the side of the starting gate and was separated from the rider at the break, ran loose during the race, was caught by the outrider after the finish and walked off under her own power.

ENTRY.NAME: Lady in a Hurry
ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved early, rail trip, middle move, stretch bid, wrong lead

ENTRY.NAME: Get'em Tiger
ENTRY.COMMENT: dueled early, backed off, re-bid 1/4, gained advantage 1/8 pole

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders two path, bid 1/4, ran on well, lost bob for 2nd

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke well, hustled clear to turn, met bid 1/4, weakened 1/8

ENTRY.NAME: Gardees World
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in the air, hit gate, lost rider

ENTRY.NAME: Shout It Out
ENTRY.COMMENT: outrun early, turn move, steadied to avoid loose horse 5/16
